    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">733.52/21</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 560</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Andrés de Llavaneras</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-02">December 2,
                            1938</date>.<lb/>[Received December 22.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the Department’s
                    strictly confidential instruction number 545, of October 31, 1938,<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d228fn5">Not printed.</note> (File No. 733.52/20) with which was
                    transmitted a copy of a despatch submitted by the American Legation at
                    Montevideo on the subject above cited, and to report that there has been no
                    change in the attitude of the Spanish Government with respect to the resumption
                    of diplomatic relations with Uruguay since the preparation of this Embassy’s
                    confidential despatch number 446, of July 15, 1938.<note n="5" xml:id="d228fn6"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I mentioned this subject to Señor Alvarez del Vayo, the Minister of State, during
                    a conversation yesterday, and he stated that while the Spanish Government
                    desires to restore such relations, and has made tentative advances, it does not
                    appear probable that they will be restored in the immediate future.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walter Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
